A repository for handing all the ~~homeworks~~ on Python.
Homework3 (environments and modules)

<h3>Python version</h3>

This program you should have Python3.10 at least, for example, Python 3.10.6. You can get it through running this line in terminal:
`sudo apt install python3.10`

<h3>OS</h3>

Note that Python 3.10 cannot be used on Windows 7 or earlier!

the OS version this code will surely work with is:

NAME="Linux Mint"
VERSION="21 (Vanessa)"
ID=linuxmint
ID_LIKE="ubuntu debian"
PRETTY_NAME="Linux Mint 21"
VERSION_ID="21"
HOME_URL="https://www.linuxmint.com/"
SUPPORT_URL="https://forums.linuxmint.com/"
BUG_REPORT_URL="http://linuxmint-troubleshooting-guide.readthedocs.io/en/latest/"
PRIVACY_POLICY_URL="https://www.linuxmint.com/"
VERSION_CODENAME=vanessa
UBUNTU_CODENAME=jammy

You can check your version with this line:
`cat /etc/os-release`

— — —

<h3>Instructions for starting the program</h3>

Create a new envoronment:
`python3.10 -m venv <Environment_name>`

Activate it:
`source environment/bin/activate`
And go to the site packages folder:
`cd ~/environment/lib/python3.10/site-packages/

Download the **requirements.txt** file and install all the modules from there. You can do this with just one line:
`pip install -r requirements.txt`

Now you should be able to run the code.

go back:
`cd ~/environment/`

download the code and run it!

